body:
Main role: integrate, configure and support the business applications and database infrastructure upon which the business relies, within agreed standards.

Blueprint of your typical tasks:

-	Provide 2nd line support for mission critical business applications;
-	Make sure each reported problem/question is resolved in a timely effective manner and tracked according to process standards;
-	Identify errors and problem trends in order to find permanent solutions;
-	Manage multiple systems and releases of varying levels of complexity;
-	Specify and maintain mechanisms for storage and access to both structured and unstructured information in support of business needs;
-	Align to guidelines and procedures to ensure appropriate consistency and quality in the service level provided;
-	Work closely with other support teams to ensure consistency and proper issue handover
-	Integrate and test components and/or systems 


Position requirements:

-	BS Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or related field 
-	Minimum 5 years of experience on a similar position;
-	Must have a strong understanding of software architectures, software lifecycle methodology and information systems development;
-	Technical skills covering, but not limited to:
o	Platforms: Windows & Linux
o	Concepts: operating systems, networking, software development, troubleshooting and diagnosis techniques
o	DBMS: SQL Server, Oracle, MySQL
-	Strong understanding of networking and infrastructure is a plus;
-	Service awareness, preferably IT infrastructure library (ITIL certification);
-	Excellent customer service and interpersonal skills;
-	Excellent verbal and written communication skills;
-	Good command of written and spoken English;
-	Ability to think logically and work within a team environment;
-	Keep him/herself abreast with the latest developments in his/her area of expertise in order to be able to contribute effectively to the business strategy.
